1. What is the difference between getElementById, getElementsByClassName, and querySelector / querySelectorAll? ==> 

Ans: => 1
    the difference between getElementById & getElementsByClassName is 
    1.getElementById is specific single  elements selecting method which is get by using getElementById
    2.getElementsByClassName is multiple elements selecting method.
    3.querySelector is as like as id type, for single elements .selector
    4.querySelectorAll is provide full dom you can access multiple things using selector